Source: The White House, RUBIO: This Is Our Hemisphere -- and President Trump Will Not Allow Our Security to be Threatened. Date on page: January 4, 2026. URL: https://www.whitehouse.gov/releases/2026/01/rubio-this-is-our-hemisphere-and-president-trump-will-not-allow-our-security-to-be-threatened/

Extracted relevant page text:
- The release says Secretary of State Marco Rubio discussed the administration's operation that apprehended Nicolás Maduro.
- Rubio stated: There is not a war against Venezuela; the U.S. is at war against drug trafficking organizations.
- Rubio stated that the U.S. did not have forces on the ground in Venezuela at the time of the interviews, but they were on the ground for about two hours when they went to capture Maduro.
- Rubio stated that the first steps are securing what is in the national interest of the United States and beneficial to the people of Venezuela, including no more drug trafficking, no more Iran/Hezbollah presence, and no more use of the oil industry to enrich U.S. adversaries.
- Rubio stated this was not an action requiring congressional approval because it was not an invasion and not an extended military operation.
- Rubio stated the United States wants Venezuela to move in a certain direction because it is good for Venezuela and in the U.S. national interest.
- Rubio stated: We retain all the options we had before this raid and this capture and this arrest until such time as changes are made.
- Rubio stated Venezuela would continue to face an oil quarantine, U.S. pressure, targeting of drug boats, seizure of sanctioned boats with court orders, and potentially other things until the issues the United States wants addressed are addressed.
- Rubio stated Maduro was not the head of state and was an illegitimate president.